    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-30T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-30T22:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.5/10–3152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador at Saigon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-31T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 31, 1952—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>912. Rptd info Paris 161. No distribution outside Department. As <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SGR1"
                        >Salan</persName> are presently in NVN I addressed questions raised in
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 888, Oct 28 to General
                        <persName>Allard</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SGR1">Salan</persName>‘s
                    chief staff. <persName>Allard</persName> stated that <gloss target="#t_VM1"
                        >VM</gloss> offensive had not endangered or deferred projected airdrop
                    operation; if anything, it may advance date operation. Typhoon damaged eleven
                    transport planes but all expected be made operational in 15 days. Help being
                    reed from <gloss target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss> which getting spare parts from
                    Philippines highly appreciated.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Allard</persName> stated friends have launched offensive operation.
                    One Group Mobile of three battalions have already crossed Black River with
                    objective of threatening from rear <gloss target="#t_VM1">VM</gloss> line
                    communication. He indicated French now have measure of <gloss target="#t_VM1"
                        >VM</gloss> offensive in that country and are taking measures cope with
                    it.</p>
                <p>Extensive press publicity abroad given <gloss target="#t_VM1">VM</gloss>
                    offensive has tended impart to operation importance not shared by consensus
                    informed opinion here. While any French Union reverse is always unfortunate and
                    gives considerable psychological advantage to enemy, regarded of secondary
                    strategic importance and its loss is not believed to constitute serious threat
                    to French military position in NVN. French <gloss target="#t_HICOM1"
                        >HICOM</gloss> is not particularly worried.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
